1046
01:08:20,804 --> 01:08:22,169
Okay, okay, okay.

1047
01:08:29,113 --> 01:08:31,946
He's slowing down, coming to a fence.
Do you see it?

1048
01:08:35,152 --> 01:08:36,642
Yeah, I see it.

1049
01:08:51,335 --> 01:08:53,428
<i>GUNNARS: Doug, if you're gonna
leave the Hummer, take the backpack.</i>

1050
01:08:53,537 --> 01:08:54,586
<i>It's the power source for the rig.</i>

1051
01:08:54,621 --> 01:08:55,636
<i>It's the power source for the rig.</i>

1052
01:09:23,400 --> 01:09:25,129
- Can you hear me?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

1053
01:09:25,235 --> 01:09:27,294
Yeah, we can hear you.
We can hear you.

1054
01:09:27,538 --> 01:09:28,596
All right.

1055
01:09:38,549 --> 01:09:40,483
What's he doing now?

1056
01:09:45,372 --> 01:09:47,203
He's pulled around
the back of the building.

1057
01:09:49,775 --> 01:09:51,868
Looks like a bomb went off.

1058
01:09:51,978 --> 01:09:55,641
Really?
We see an intact structure here.

1059
01:09:56,482 --> 01:09:59,576
<i>- No damage?
- No, none.</i>

1060
01:10:01,354 --> 01:10:03,618
Looks like a vehicle's inside.

1061
01:10:03,723 --> 01:10:05,623
An ambulance. You see that?

1062
01:10:06,626 --> 01:10:08,651
No. Nothing.

1063
01:10:32,285 --> 01:10:33,718
See anything?

1064
01:10:34,453 --> 01:10:36,512
PRYZWARRA: He's dead ahead of you.

1065
01:10:36,622 --> 01:10:38,522
Doug, he's pulling Minuti out of the car.

1066
01:10:38,624 --> 01:10:39,716
Where?

1067
01:10:39,825 --> 01:10:41,850
All right, now pan to the right.
Pan to the right.

1068
01:10:41,961 --> 01:10:43,189
- More right.
- DENNY: You got him.

1069
01:10:43,296 --> 01:10:44,820
Yeah, he's dragging him out of the car.

1070
01:10:44,931 --> 01:10:46,228
Do you see him?

1071
01:10:46,332 --> 01:10:48,596
- Yeah.
- Yes. Right in front of you.

1072
01:10:48,701 --> 01:10:50,498
Boost the audio for me.

1073
01:10:50,603 --> 01:10:52,161
Audio boosted.

1074
01:10:52,638 --> 01:10:55,106
<i>DENNY: Turn around.
Turn around behind you.</i>

1075
01:10:56,008 --> 01:10:57,908
<i>- Larry?
- Pan back to the right.</i>

1076
01:10:58,511 --> 01:10:59,876
<i>- You've got him now.
- Where is he?</i>

1077
01:10:59,979 --> 01:11:02,072
He's being dragged on the concrete.

1078
01:11:04,684 --> 01:11:06,015
Larry!

1079
01:11:10,656 --> 01:11:12,283
What's that sound?

1080
01:11:13,159 --> 01:11:14,786
<i>What's the sound?</i>

1081
01:11:15,461 --> 01:11:19,591
He's pouring some kind of accelerant
over Agent Minuti.

1082
01:11:19,699 --> 01:11:23,032
I think it's the diesel fuel,
like at the ferry.

1083
01:11:32,044 --> 01:11:33,671
He's waking up.

1084
01:11:33,779 --> 01:11:37,010
Brace yourselves. I think
you're about to witness a murder.

1085
01:11:37,116 --> 01:11:38,344
[GUN FIRES]

1086
01:12:42,415 --> 01:12:44,076
<i>[CHATTERING ON RADIO]</i>

1087
01:12:50,356 --> 01:12:52,381
If we hadn't sent him there,
he wouldn't be dead now.

1088
01:12:52,491 --> 01:12:55,255
No, he was already dead from the ferry.
We just changed how he died.

1089
01:12:55,361 --> 01:12:56,453
We don't know that.

1090
01:12:56,562 --> 01:12:57,927
He could've been standing
right next to you,

1091
01:12:58,030 --> 01:12:59,054
right until we sent that note.

1092
01:12:59,165 --> 01:13:01,429
<i>SHANTI: You'd need a branching
multiple universe for that to happen.</i>

1093
01:13:01,534 --> 01:13:04,298
<i>DENNY: Oh, come on.
We can't change anything.</i>

1094
01:13:04,403 --> 01:13:07,736
We didn't change anything.
That's what I've been trying to tell you.

1095
01:13:07,840 --> 01:13:09,831
I'll tell you what we did.

1096
01:13:10,443 --> 01:13:13,742
The suspect used a stolen Blazer
to case the dock.

1097
01:13:13,846 --> 01:13:17,805
So now he has a truck big enough
to drive a bomb onto the ferry.

1098
01:13:18,417 --> 01:13:20,408
<i>Now Larry shows up, right?</i>

1099
01:13:21,020 --> 01:13:23,853
Larry puts bullet holes
through the windshield.

1100
01:13:23,956 --> 01:13:26,516
- You want a mask?
- No. No, I'm good, thanks.

1101
01:13:26,625 --> 01:13:28,650
Larry puts bullet holes
through the windshield,

1102
01:13:28,761 --> 01:13:32,094
<i>leaves blood all over the back seat,
so now our bomber needs a new truck,</i>

1103
01:13:32,198 --> 01:13:34,598
you understand? Claire's truck.

1104
01:13:36,535 --> 01:13:37,866
<i>You hungry?</i>

1105
01:13:37,970 --> 01:13:39,062
Yeah, we changed one thing,

1106
01:13:39,171 --> 01:13:41,901
but by changing one thing,
we didn't change anything.

1107
01:13:42,007 --> 01:13:43,702
<i>What's on TV?</i>

1108
01:14:20,746 --> 01:14:21,872
Hey, hey, hey, we got a name.

1109
01:14:22,515 --> 01:14:24,176
- Carroll Oerstadt.
- WOMAN: What?

1110
01:14:24,283 --> 01:14:27,252
- KEVIN: Who is that?
- Owner of that bait camp Doug found.

1111
01:14:27,353 --> 01:14:30,447
Truck registration,
airboat registration, match.

1112
01:14:30,556 --> 01:14:31,614
And another property.

1113
01:14:31,724 --> 01:14:34,750
5874 Mullie Ave., Ninth Ward,
New Orleans.

1114
01:14:34,860 --> 01:14:37,055
- Is this a he or a she?
- It's a he. Let's go.

1115
01:15:11,297 --> 01:15:12,491
Clear!

1116
01:15:40,707 --> 01:15:42,868
<i>CARLIN: Testing, one, two, three, four.</i>

1117
01:15:43,844 --> 01:15:46,108
<i>Testing, one, two, three, four.</i>

1118
01:15:47,681 --> 01:15:49,579
<i>ATF New Orleans, conducting
interview with Carroll Oerstadt.</i>

1119
01:15:49,614 --> 01:15:51,478
<i>ATF New Orleans, conducting
interview with Carroll Oerstadt.</i>

1120
01:15:52,419 --> 01:15:54,114
<i>You've waived your right
to counsel, right?</i>

1121
01:15:54,221 --> 01:15:55,984
<i>- OERSTADT: Yes, sir.
- Okay.</i>

1122
01:15:57,291 --> 01:16:00,556
<i>I'm fascinated with your precision.</i>

1123
01:16:01,495 --> 01:16:04,293
It's not very often we see that level
of expertise around here,

1124
01:16:04,398 --> 01:16:06,798
and if it's all right with you,
I'd like to use this interview

1125
01:16:06,900 --> 01:16:10,631
to educate my colleagues
in law enforcement.

1126
01:16:10,737 --> 01:16:13,331
- Yes, sir.
- Good. Good.

1127
01:16:13,574 --> 01:16:14,836
Let's talk about motive.

1128
01:16:14,942 --> 01:16:18,537
Why would you use explosives
against the US Navy?

1129
01:16:19,980 --> 01:16:24,280
- Correction, sir. US Government.
- US Government.

1130
01:16:25,118 --> 01:16:28,417
It says here that you tried
to enlist in the Marines.

1131
01:16:28,522 --> 01:16:30,353
You were rejected.
You tried to enlist in the Army,

1132
01:16:30,457 --> 01:16:32,482
you were rejected again.

1133
01:16:32,593 --> 01:16:34,857
Why do you think they did that?

1134
01:16:36,396 --> 01:16:38,762
Because they don't want patriots.

1135
01:16:39,466 --> 01:16:42,560
The military no longer recognizes
commitment and purpose.

1136
01:16:43,070 --> 01:16:46,528
They thought I was overcommitted
and psychologically unstable.

1137
01:16:46,640 --> 01:16:48,403
They didn't want to understand
my value.

1138
01:16:50,160 --> 01:16:51,889
They understand it now.

1139
01:16:52,528 --> 01:16:54,462
I believe so. Yes, sir.

1140
01:16:58,134 --> 01:17:00,534
- You're ATF, right?
- Yes, I am.

1141
01:17:01,404 --> 01:17:03,872
- Got a smoke?
- No, I don't. But I can get you one.

1142
01:17:03,973 --> 01:17:05,440
- Would you like one?
- Yes.

1143
01:17:05,541 --> 01:17:08,339
Okay. Anything you want to say,
just talk into the mike.

1144
01:17:08,444 --> 01:17:11,641
A man can always use more alcohol,
tobacco and firearms.

1145
01:17:11,747 --> 01:17:13,772
I can think of one more thing.

1146
01:17:17,553 --> 01:17:19,612
<i>It's like the Revolutionary War,
you know what I mean?</i>

1147
01:17:19,722 --> 01:17:22,850
<i>"One man's terrorist
is another man's patriot, " isn't it?</i>

1148
01:17:23,592 --> 01:17:25,617
<i>CARLIN: Yeah?
OERSTADT: Exactly.</i>

1149
01:17:25,728 --> 01:17:27,320
<i>- Yeah.
- You get it.</i>

1150
01:17:29,465 --> 01:17:32,457
- This wasn't about revenge.
- What was it about?

1151
01:17:35,538 --> 01:17:36,732
Destiny.

1152
01:17:37,073 --> 01:17:38,267
Destiny?

1153
01:17:39,575 --> 01:17:41,167
You've been asking me
about my motives.

1154
01:17:41,277 --> 01:17:42,801
- Right. Right.
- My methods.

1155
01:17:44,347 --> 01:17:45,905
They're all connected.

1156
01:17:46,582 --> 01:17:48,015
Everything's connected.

1157
01:17:48,117 --> 01:17:50,415
Okay.
How was Claire Kuchever connected?

1158
01:17:50,519 --> 01:17:51,986
I needed a car.

1159
01:17:52,088 --> 01:17:53,646
- And that's it?
- No, well, something

1160
01:17:53,756 --> 01:17:55,724
- that couldn't be traced back to me.
- Right.

1161
01:17:55,825 --> 01:17:58,589
I had one ready till that cop showed up.

1162
01:17:59,228 --> 01:18:01,856
That cop was a federal agent.

1163
01:18:01,964 --> 01:18:04,330
Lawrence Minuti. My partner.
You shot him.

1164
01:18:04,433 --> 01:18:07,402
He... I was about to burn him
and he was waking up, you know?

1165
01:18:07,503 --> 01:18:09,095
I mean, I'm not cruel.

1166
01:18:11,607 --> 01:18:15,745
Well, why didn't you "do that"
for Claire Kuchever?

1167
01:18:17,446 --> 01:18:22,907
Well, because I needed her
to look like a ferry victim,

1168
01:18:23,019 --> 01:18:24,199
- and a bullet would've given it away.
- I see.

1169
01:18:24,234 --> 01:18:25,380
- And a bullet would've given it away.
- I see.

1170
01:18:25,488 --> 01:18:28,821
I went to her house
on the pretense of buying her car.

1171
01:18:28,924 --> 01:18:32,155
I took her from behind, taped her mouth
and threw a hood over her head.

1172
01:18:32,261 --> 01:18:33,228
Then?

1173
01:18:33,329 --> 01:18:36,355
<i>I bound her wrists and her ankles
and I drove her back to my place.</i>

1174
01:18:36,465 --> 01:18:38,296
<i>I loaded the device into her car</i>

1175
01:18:38,401 --> 01:18:39,959
<i>and then I soaked her
with the gasoline.</i>

1176
01:18:40,069 --> 01:18:41,161
Jesus.

1177
01:18:41,270 --> 01:18:42,294
And?

1178
01:18:42,538 --> 01:18:43,937
I think you know
what happened after that.

1179
01:18:44,040 --> 01:18:45,940
No, I don't know. I want you to tell me.
You gotta talk.

1180
01:18:46,042 --> 01:18:48,067
I mean, you know, come on, hero.
What happened after that?

1181
01:18:48,177 --> 01:18:49,337
I'll tell you what happened after that.

1182
01:18:49,445 --> 01:18:52,881
You killed 543 people.
How do you feel about that?

1183
01:18:58,020 --> 01:19:01,649
I think that you were a murderer
right from the beginning.

1184
01:19:04,160 --> 01:19:07,721
Sometimes a little human collateral
is the cost of freedom.

1185
01:19:07,830 --> 01:19:09,695
To me,
those people were war casualties,

1186
01:19:09,799 --> 01:19:11,699
<i>but to you, they're just evidence.</i>

1187
01:19:11,801 --> 01:19:14,235
That'll do. We got him.

1188
01:19:14,336 --> 01:19:15,303
<i>CARLIN: What'd you say?</i>

1189
01:19:15,538 --> 01:19:19,269
You think you know what's coming?
You don't have a clue.

1190
01:19:19,375 --> 01:19:21,366
I know where you're going.

1191
01:19:21,777 --> 01:19:25,440
I know you're gonna be away
for a long time. I know that.

1192
01:19:26,449 --> 01:19:28,940
- This case will never even go to trial.
- No?

1193
01:19:30,486 --> 01:19:33,512
- 'Cause I seen what's coming.
- Did... Have you? What?

1194
01:19:34,290 --> 01:19:37,453
What is in this glass?
You've seen what's coming, huh?

1195
01:19:37,560 --> 01:19:39,653
Okay, what's coming? You tell me.

1196
01:19:40,629 --> 01:19:43,291
I told you earlier I have a destiny,

1197
01:19:43,399 --> 01:19:44,730
a purpose.

1198
01:19:45,434 --> 01:19:48,528
Satan reasons like man,
but God thinks of eternity.

1199
01:19:49,105 --> 01:19:53,633
Well, I prostrate myself before a world
that's going to hell in a handbag,

1200
01:19:53,742 --> 01:19:56,836
'cause in all eternity,
I am here and I will be remembered.

1201
01:19:56,946 --> 01:19:58,538
That's destiny.

1202
01:19:59,248 --> 01:20:01,011
A bomb has a destiny,

1203
01:20:01,550 --> 01:20:04,610
a predetermined fate
set by the hand of its creator.

1204
01:20:04,720 --> 01:20:08,019
And anyone who tries to alter
that destiny will be destroyed.

1205
01:20:08,124 --> 01:20:11,491
Anyone who tries to stop it
from happening will cause it to happen.

1206
01:20:11,594 --> 01:20:13,494
And that's what you don't understand.

1207
01:20:13,596 --> 01:20:17,430
We're not here to coexist.
I'm here to win.

1208
01:20:17,800 --> 01:20:20,633
So you'd better have
some divine intervention, buddy.

1209
01:20:21,437 --> 01:20:23,564
You're gonna need it.

1210
01:20:23,873 --> 01:20:27,400
You'd better have some K-Y.
You're gonna need it.

1211
01:20:39,321 --> 01:20:41,346
What am I supposed to do?

1212
01:20:42,725 --> 01:20:45,125
- We're shutting you down.
- What?

1213
01:20:45,628 --> 01:20:46,617
Yeah, we got what we need.

1214
01:20:46,729 --> 01:20:49,197
The forensics, the suspect,
a confession. We're done.

1215
01:20:49,298 --> 01:20:52,790
Sir, perhaps we should continue
and watch the actual crime.

1216
01:20:52,902 --> 01:20:54,426
- The ferry bombing.
- Right. He's right.

1217
01:20:54,537 --> 01:20:56,664
I mean, we can't just
go on the confession alone.

1218
01:20:56,772 --> 01:20:59,002
We need an airtight case.
We need to collect more evidence.

1219
01:20:59,108 --> 01:21:01,372
Well, collecting evidence
would've been fine, Agent Carly.

1220
01:21:01,477 --> 01:21:04,037
- You took it a little further than that.
- Agent Carlin. Carlin.

1221
01:21:04,146 --> 01:21:05,238
My name is Carlin, not Carly.

1222
01:21:05,347 --> 01:21:07,907
We had protocols in place.
There's strict protocols.

1223
01:21:08,017 --> 01:21:10,713
And then you had to push it,
and now an agent's dead.

1224
01:21:10,819 --> 01:21:13,083
Sir, by one theory,
that already happened.

1225
01:21:13,189 --> 01:21:16,454
We're done. Power it down.
Pack it up. On to the next case.

1226
01:21:17,193 --> 01:21:18,956
- What about Claire?
- What...

1227
01:21:19,528 --> 01:21:21,519
Lookit, charging Oerstadt
in the Kuchever murder

1228
01:21:21,630 --> 01:21:24,224
is gonna raise too many questions
about how we obtained the evidence.

1229
01:21:24,333 --> 01:21:25,732
I understand that, sir,
but what about Claire?

1230
01:21:25,834 --> 01:21:26,892
Are we just gonna drop the case?

1231
01:21:27,002 --> 01:21:29,436
We got him on the ferry bombing,
we got him on killing a federal agent.

1232
01:21:29,538 --> 01:21:31,836
- That's enough to get him the needle.
- I cannot accept that, sir.

1233
01:21:31,941 --> 01:21:34,409
Well, you know, I don't give a rat's ass
what you can accept.

1234
01:21:34,510 --> 01:21:36,944
- She doesn't matter.
- He's gonna kill her.

1235
01:21:37,279 --> 01:21:40,771
- In 12 hours, he's gonna kill her.
- He killed her four days ago.

1236
01:21:40,883 --> 01:21:43,545
You were at the funeral.
What's wrong with you?

1237
01:21:47,489 --> 01:21:49,047
It had to happen.

1238
01:21:49,191 --> 01:21:52,524
I delayed turning in my report
till we caught the guy.

1239
01:21:53,229 --> 01:21:54,924
Hey, mission accomplished.

1240
01:21:55,397 --> 01:21:57,524
This is a victory, Doug.

1241
01:22:04,573 --> 01:22:07,599
Hey. Now, my job is closure.

1242
01:22:07,710 --> 01:22:10,235
Your job is to help facilitate
that closure.

1243
01:22:10,346 --> 01:22:12,610
Then you tell me,
what do I tell her father?

1244
01:22:12,715 --> 01:22:14,774
We caught the son of a bitch.

1245
01:22:14,883 --> 01:22:16,009
We can't save the victims.

1246
01:22:16,118 --> 01:22:19,383
It's not our job
to make the relatives feel better.

1247
01:22:19,788 --> 01:22:23,952
We lose everything that we care about.
Those are your words.

1248
01:22:25,027 --> 01:22:28,019
Doug, it's not your fault
that Claire dies.

1249
01:22:30,599 --> 01:22:32,533
Yeah, that's one theory.

1250
01:22:37,072 --> 01:22:39,905
<i>MAN ON TV:
Lieutenant Junior Grade Dianne Kerry.</i>

1251
01:22:40,309 --> 01:22:42,072
<i>Martin Kyle.</i>

1252
01:22:43,279 --> 01:22:45,975
<i>Commander Francis Lacey, retired.</i>

1253
01:22:46,515 --> 01:22:48,278
<i>Elaine Lacey.</i>

1254
01:22:49,585 --> 01:22:52,110
<i>Chief Petty Officer Darren McAndrews.</i>

1255
01:22:52,955 --> 01:22:54,980
<i>Lorraine McAndrews.</i>

1256
01:22:55,090 --> 01:22:56,079
<i>[SINGING]</i>

1257
01:22:56,191 --> 01:22:59,126
<i>Electronics Technician Lisa Melville.</i>

1258
01:22:59,728 --> 01:23:02,526
<i>Chaplain Rabbi Benjamin Mendelsson.</i>

1259
01:24:11,600 --> 01:24:12,897
[PHONE RINGING]

1260
01:24:19,441 --> 01:24:21,102
Denny? It's Doug.

1261
01:24:21,210 --> 01:24:23,872
Well, I can't say
I wasn't expecting this call.

1262
01:24:24,646 --> 01:24:27,171
Look, you know what happens
if you try this.

1263
01:24:27,282 --> 01:24:28,874
We both know what happens if I don't.

1264
01:24:28,984 --> 01:24:33,318
Well, not a lot of guinea pigs volunteer
to die in the name of science.

1265
01:24:33,422 --> 01:24:34,912
Well, then we have to make sure

1266
01:24:35,023 --> 01:24:37,287
I end up somewhere
besides the morgue.

1267
01:24:37,960 --> 01:24:39,291
Can you help me?

1268
01:24:43,866 --> 01:24:46,130
I'll see you when you get here.

1269
01:24:47,603 --> 01:24:48,661
Doug?

1270
01:24:54,810 --> 01:24:59,770
Do me a favor.
When you finish, turn off the lights.

1271
01:25:20,269 --> 01:25:23,727
You do that one more time,
you set off every alarm in the joint.

1272
01:25:28,143 --> 01:25:29,235
Can't take it.

1273
01:25:29,378 --> 01:25:30,936
Gotta keep the mass
as low as possible.

1274
01:25:31,046 --> 01:25:33,139
You gotta take everything off.

1275
01:25:38,387 --> 01:25:41,879
- You can keep your underwear on.
- Thank you very much.

1276
01:25:42,458 --> 01:25:46,258
Thought you said you didn't believe
in changing the past.

1277
01:25:46,628 --> 01:25:49,256
Right. Well, I also believe in God.

1278
01:25:49,364 --> 01:25:50,763
Just don't tell anyone.

1279
01:25:50,866 --> 01:25:52,993
- I'm gonna tell everybody.
- Yeah?

1280
01:25:53,135 --> 01:25:55,968
You know, when I open up the throttle
on this thing...

1281
01:25:56,071 --> 01:25:59,472
Yeah, I know. EM field, flatline. I got it.

1282
01:25:59,908 --> 01:26:02,638
Thing of it is,
no matter how clever we think we are,

1283
01:26:02,744 --> 01:26:05,304
the most probable outcome
of our little experiment

1284
01:26:05,414 --> 01:26:09,145
is that four and a half days ago
you get a call from the coroner's office.

1285
01:26:09,251 --> 01:26:11,412
"Hey, Agent Carlin,
I want you to come down here.

1286
01:26:11,520 --> 01:26:13,283
"There's something you should see."

1287
01:26:13,388 --> 01:26:16,357
And next thing you know,
you're standing over a corpse

1288
01:26:16,458 --> 01:26:17,891
and it's you.

1289
01:26:18,327 --> 01:26:23,594
Well, you can be wrong a million times.
You only gotta be right once.

1290
01:26:23,699 --> 01:26:26,031
Besides, I think I'd remember
if that happened, right?

1291
01:26:26,134 --> 01:26:28,159
So I gotta face out toward you?

1292
01:26:28,270 --> 01:26:31,103
Yeah, face out.
Just like the note, only bigger.

1293
01:26:32,674 --> 01:26:34,801
- You ready?
- No.

1294
01:26:36,178 --> 01:26:38,408
You don't have to do this.

1295
01:26:40,115 --> 01:26:41,980
What if I already have?

1296
01:26:42,784 --> 01:26:43,910
Right.

1297
01:26:57,266 --> 01:26:58,324
Doug?

1298
01:27:00,335 --> 01:27:01,393
<i>DENNY: Doug?</i>

1299
01:27:01,737 --> 01:27:04,262
Hey. Hello?

1300
01:27:04,540 --> 01:27:06,474
<i>- You okay in there?
- Yeah.</i>

1301
01:27:06,642 --> 01:27:08,405
- You good?
- Yeah, yeah, I'm good.

1302
01:27:08,510 --> 01:27:11,104
I'm beside myself.

1303
01:27:13,882 --> 01:27:15,679
<i>Am I still here?</i>

1304
01:27:15,784 --> 01:27:17,115
For now. You ready?

1305
01:27:17,219 --> 01:27:18,777
<i>- Yeah, I'm ready.
- All right.</i>

1306
01:27:18,887 --> 01:27:20,684
<i>Looking forward to walking up to you
four days ago</i>

1307
01:27:20,789 --> 01:27:21,915
<i>and blowing your mind, though.</i>

1308
01:27:22,024 --> 01:27:23,423
Well, if that happens,
maybe you can tell me

1309
01:27:23,525 --> 01:27:24,890
what it's like to meet your younger self.

1310
01:27:24,993 --> 01:27:26,824
<i>All right, I'll let you know.</i>

1311
01:27:26,929 --> 01:27:31,662
All right, remember, the ferry blows
at 10:50 on Fat Tuesday, okay?

1312
01:27:32,601 --> 01:27:33,659
<i>Yeah.</i>

1313
01:27:34,970 --> 01:27:36,301
Here we go.

1314
01:27:37,439 --> 01:27:38,633
See you yesterday.

1315
01:27:38,740 --> 01:27:40,105
God willing.

1316
01:28:04,967 --> 01:28:05,991
<i>DENNY: Good, good.</i>

1317
01:28:06,101 --> 01:28:07,500
<i>- You don't have to do this.
- CLAIRE: Hello?</i>

1318
01:28:07,603 --> 01:28:08,661
<i>CARLIN: Maybe I already have.</i>

1319
01:28:08,770 --> 01:28:10,294
<i>Maybe I already have.</i>

1320
01:28:13,442 --> 01:28:15,433
NURSE: What the hell?
DOCTOR: All right, hold on, everybody.

1321
01:28:15,544 --> 01:28:18,274
The reserve generators should kick in.
Nobody move.

1322
01:28:18,380 --> 01:28:20,211
That was interesting.

1323
01:28:20,315 --> 01:28:21,543
[CLATTERING]

1324
01:28:23,785 --> 01:28:25,275
- Doctor!
- Who the hell is that?

1325
01:28:25,387 --> 01:28:27,218
Where'd he come from?

1326
01:28:28,724 --> 01:28:32,057
All right, let's get him into Trauma.
Trauma 2, Trauma 2!

1327
01:28:37,366 --> 01:28:38,924
DOCTOR: This is weird.

1328
01:28:40,736 --> 01:28:42,260
- NURSE: Defib.
- Clear!

1329
01:28:42,804 --> 01:28:44,567
Recharge it again.

1330
01:28:45,374 --> 01:28:46,602
Clear!

1331
01:28:47,009 --> 01:28:48,874
- Recharge to 300.
- Charging.

1332
01:28:49,411 --> 01:28:50,605
Clear!

1333
01:28:52,314 --> 01:28:56,852
Resume CPR. One, two, three,
four, five, six, seven, eight.

1334
01:29:22,911 --> 01:29:24,503
<i>MAN ON TV: Thirty-four degrees.</i>

1335
01:29:24,613 --> 01:29:27,138
<i>Forty-nine was our low temperature
at the airport.</i>

1336
01:29:27,249 --> 01:29:30,616
<i>Gonna be at that
or just maybe above that for tonight.</i>

1337
01:29:30,719 --> 01:29:33,381
<i>Let me show you why.
Look, the winds are starting...</i>

1338
01:29:52,220 --> 01:29:56,088
...a few of them come back.
- I'm thinking about getting a tattoo.

1339
01:29:57,225 --> 01:29:58,385
- Whoa!
- I'm a federal agent.

1340
01:29:58,493 --> 01:30:00,859
I need your keys. I need a vehicle.

1341
01:30:00,962 --> 01:30:02,623
There's keys in the truck there.

1342
01:30:02,731 --> 01:30:04,756
Which one? Right here?
Put your hands down.

1343
01:30:04,866 --> 01:30:08,063
Hands on the table.
Hold your donut. Hands right there.

1344
01:30:09,871 --> 01:30:11,099
Water it.

1345
01:30:11,806 --> 01:30:13,103
[SIREN BLARING]

1346
01:30:33,061 --> 01:30:35,894
<i>MAN ON TV: This might be a metaphor
for existence itself.</i>

1347
01:30:35,997 --> 01:30:41,435
<i>A fish struggles instinctively
against an almost formless antagonist.</i>

1348
01:30:41,536 --> 01:30:43,436
<i>The fish is a largemouth bass.</i>

1349
01:30:57,802 --> 01:30:59,861
<i>MAN ON RADIO:
Here's the news at 8:30.</i>

1350
01:31:00,104 --> 01:31:02,971
<i>Federal officials are still baffled
by the massive blackout</i>

1351
01:31:03,074 --> 01:31:06,976
<i>that darkened the entire eastern half
of the country early this morning.</i>

1352
01:31:22,893 --> 01:31:23,985
[MUFFLED GROANING]

1353
01:33:01,992 --> 01:33:03,186
Hey!

1354
01:33:41,565 --> 01:33:43,089
[MUFFLED MOANING]

1355
01:34:25,109 --> 01:34:26,508
Jesus.

1356
01:34:31,415 --> 01:34:32,780
[GRUNTS]

1357
01:34:32,883 --> 01:34:35,750
Wait a minute.
Hey, it's okay. Wait a minute!

1358
01:34:35,853 --> 01:34:37,650
Listen. Claire!

1359
01:34:37,755 --> 01:34:40,588
I'm a federal agent. Hang on, hang on.

1360
01:34:41,492 --> 01:34:43,084
All right, it's okay. It's okay. It's okay.

1361
01:34:43,194 --> 01:34:45,754
I'm a federal agent. It's okay. It's okay.

1362
01:34:46,931 --> 01:34:48,694
You're safe. You're all right, okay?

1363
01:34:48,799 --> 01:34:53,065
I'm a federal agent. You're safe.
You're safe. Look at me. Come here.

1364
01:34:53,170 --> 01:34:55,434
You're safe. He's gone. All right?

1365
01:34:57,842 --> 01:35:00,242
- [CRYING] Get me out of here!
- All right. All right.

1366
01:35:00,344 --> 01:35:02,141
Get me out of here!

1367
01:35:02,446 --> 01:35:06,007
It's all right. It's okay. It's okay.

1368
01:35:07,651 --> 01:35:10,449
- Get me out of here.
- All right, let me get your feet.

1369
01:35:10,554 --> 01:35:13,250
It's all right. It's all right. It's all right.

1370
01:35:16,060 --> 01:35:18,426
Hey, look at me. Look at me.

1371
01:35:18,529 --> 01:35:20,861
I'm gonna get you out of here, okay?

1372
01:35:20,965 --> 01:35:22,432
All right.

1373
01:35:37,114 --> 01:35:39,912
How'd you know
there'd be keys in this truck?

1374
01:35:40,017 --> 01:35:42,815
That's a good question. I didn't know.

1375
01:35:46,490 --> 01:35:48,549
- He's a terrorist?
- Yeah.

1376
01:35:48,659 --> 01:35:53,062
His name is Carroll Oerstadt.
I'm a part of a special surveillance unit.

1377
01:35:53,163 --> 01:35:54,687
We've been tracking him.

1378
01:35:54,798 --> 01:35:59,132
He's planning on blowing up
the Canal Street Ferry today at 10:50.

1379
01:36:02,573 --> 01:36:05,337
- So we're going to the police?
- No, it's too complicated.

1380
01:36:05,442 --> 01:36:07,637
By the time we get them up to speed,
the ferry will be gone.

1381
01:36:07,745 --> 01:36:09,406
We gotta go
straight to the Algiers dock.

1382
01:36:09,513 --> 01:36:11,913
I don't think you're gonna make it.
You're losing too much blood.

1383
01:36:12,016 --> 01:36:15,417
No, I gotta make it. I only got an hour
and 40 minutes to catch up to this guy.

1384
01:36:15,519 --> 01:36:18,955
What if you don't make it?
What happens then?

1385
01:36:19,056 --> 01:36:21,047
If I don't make it...

1386
01:36:23,027 --> 01:36:24,460
What?

1387
01:36:25,562 --> 01:36:26,620
Your house is on the way.

1388
01:36:26,730 --> 01:36:28,391
We'll go by your house,
and I'll get cleaned up.

1389
01:36:28,499 --> 01:36:32,299
- I'll drop you off. All right?
- All right.

1390
01:36:33,437 --> 01:36:34,927
Hey, Ginger.

1391
01:36:35,739 --> 01:36:37,536
She hates strangers.

1392
01:36:37,808 --> 01:36:38,900
You need anything?

1393
01:36:39,009 --> 01:36:40,943
You get cleaned up.
I'll take care of this.

1394
01:36:41,045 --> 01:36:44,412
- You sure? I could bind that for you.
- No, I'm sure. You go ahead.

1395
01:36:44,515 --> 01:36:47,143
I'm gonna need to borrow
one of your boyfriend's jackets, though.

1396
01:36:47,251 --> 01:36:48,309
Sure.

1397
01:37:35,632 --> 01:37:37,600
Hey, listen.

1398
01:37:37,701 --> 01:37:40,295
- You shouldn't wear that.
- What?

1399
01:37:41,305 --> 01:37:42,670
Why don't you put on a different one?

1400
01:37:42,773 --> 01:37:45,936
The blue and white one. Anything.
It's just...

1401
01:37:46,043 --> 01:37:47,067
Just trust me.

1402
01:37:47,177 --> 01:37:51,307
The victim wore a dress like that
and it wouldn't be good.

1403
01:37:52,916 --> 01:37:54,645
- Okay.
- Trust me.

1404
01:37:55,052 --> 01:37:59,580
All right, I'll go change. I'll be right out.

1405
